Spain Aims to Regularize 500,000 Undeclared Jobs, Expansion Says

-- B y   E m m a   R o s s - T h o m a s
-- 
2011-03-31T07:18:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/spain-aims-to-regularize-500-000-undeclared-jobs-expansion-says.html
Spain  plans a four-month suspension
of rules on undeclared workers to encourage 500,000 shadow-
economy jobs to be registered with authorities, Expansion
reported, citing Labor Ministry advisers.  The measure would reduce the unemployment rate by three to
four percentage points, the newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
